## **vim tricks**

**when creating a file use a back-up example below, use .b** 

```jsx
k run pod —image=nginx —dry-run=client  -o yaml > pod_name.yaml.b
```

**tricks to find and replace the word** 

1. when seraching some stuff use “ / “ to enter find mode 
2. then shft + c to replace the word. 

tricks to indent a line the “ >  “ or “ < “ is an arrow key 

- shift + >  OR shift + <

tricks to add a line below and above 

- o → add line below
- O → add line above

tricks to indent a line of code 

- shift v  → to enter block mode
- highlight the line of code using arrows
- . to repeat

copy paste of block of text 

- shift v
- highlight  then  y = to copy , p = paste
